1
00:00:00,222 --> 00:00:02,976

2
00:00:02,976 --> 00:00:05,703

3
00:00:05,703 --> 00:00:10,783
Krishna knows how to look at that tree.

4
00:00:10,783 --> 00:00:12,733
A tree of Veda.

5
00:00:12,733 --> 00:00:16,492

6
00:00:16,492 --> 00:00:19,061
And we're told: what comes from there?

7
00:00:19,061 --> 00:00:23,860
Veda-pushpa. The flower of the tree of Veda

8
00:00:23,860 --> 00:00:27,001
comes in the form of Vedanta.

9
00:00:27,001 --> 00:00:30,028
The Vedanta sutra.

10
00:00:30,028 --> 00:00:31,832
Dig-darshan.

11
00:00:31,832 --> 00:00:32,297
Telling us what?

12
00:00:32,297 --> 00:00:34,137
Anandam brahmano viduh.

13
00:00:34,137 --> 00:00:38,695
ananda mayo bhyasat

14
00:00:38,695 --> 00:00:45,302
The original source of everything is happiness personified.

15
00:00:45,302 --> 00:00:47,170
If you can read it.

16
00:00:47,170 --> 00:00:56,497
That's what Gurudev told me once, when we were at the time of Radhashtami.

17
00:00:56,497 --> 00:01:00,209
Singing all these songs of Bhaktivinod Thakur.

18
00:01:00,209 --> 00:01:03,343
Where it's says, I don't know the line, but:

19
00:01:03,343 --> 00:01:08,012
vede bole... something... radha cha...

20
00:01:08,012 --> 00:01:11,825
Saying that, more or less, I mean, paraphrasing, that:

21
00:01:11,825 --> 00:01:16,542
All the Vedas declare, sing and declare

22
00:01:16,542 --> 00:01:23,583
that Krishna is the property of Radharani and Her girlfriends.

23
00:01:23,583 --> 00:01:28,041
And I'm saying: Maharaj, how can he say that?

24
00:01:28,041 --> 00:01:29,911
I mean I'm saying that in like:

25
00:01:29,911 --> 00:01:35,090
"Wow! That's an outrageous statement!"

26
00:01:35,090 --> 00:01:37,171
By one meaning of the word outrageous.

27
00:01:37,171 --> 00:01:40,158
It's astonishing, it's shocking!

28
00:01:40,158 --> 00:01:43,395
Bhaktivinod Thakur: "All the Vedas are saying this."

29
00:01:43,395 --> 00:01:46,409
Really? Is that what they're saying?

30
00:01:46,409 --> 00:01:48,257
If you are listening to them

31
00:01:48,257 --> 00:01:51,055
and they don't appear to be saying that,

32
00:01:51,055 --> 00:01:56,132
who's a better observer: rishi? you?

33
00:01:56,132 --> 00:02:01,926
Who cannot hear, see, taste, touch, smell that divine substance?

34
00:02:01,926 --> 00:02:06,092
Or the connoisseur: Bhaktivinod Thakur.

35
00:02:06,092 --> 00:02:09,053
So Gurudev answered it very beautifully, he said:

36
00:02:09,053 --> 00:02:14,339
"He can say that because he has a vision of the whole".

37
00:02:14,339 --> 00:02:14,934
That's how.

38
00:02:14,934 --> 00:02:16,575
If you look at the part,

39
00:02:16,575 --> 00:02:19,510
if you look at the tree without the mango

40
00:02:19,510 --> 00:02:22,375
it's confusing.

41
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:25,217
If this is a mango tree why are there no mangos?

42
00:02:25,217 --> 00:02:31,854
Well, there, Vedanta-pushpa...

43
00:02:31,854 --> 00:02:33,608
ananda mayo bhyasat

44
00:02:33,608 --> 00:02:35,174
anavritti shabdah

45
00:02:35,174 --> 00:02:38,053
nigama kalpa taror galitam phalam

46
00:02:38,053 --> 00:02:42,168
shuka-mukhad amrita-drava samyutam

47
00:02:42,168 --> 00:02:45,649
pibata bhagavatam rasam alayam

48
00:02:45,649 --> 00:02:52,808
muhur aho rasika bhuvi bhavukah
(SB 1.1.3)

49
00:02:52,808 --> 00:02:53,807
What they say?

50
00:02:53,807 --> 00:03:01,174
The mature, ripened fruit of the tree of Vedic literature.

51
00:03:01,174 --> 00:03:02,053
Then we understand.

52
00:03:02,053 --> 00:03:07,728
When you see the fruit, taste the fruit,

53
00:03:07,728 --> 00:03:11,340
relish the fruit, the substance

54
00:03:11,340 --> 00:03:13,134
muhur aho rasika...

55
00:03:13,134 --> 00:03:20,239
repeatedly relishing this divine nectarine substance

56
00:03:20,239 --> 00:03:22,255
for those.

57
00:03:22,255 --> 00:03:26,816
They understand: that's the purpose of the flower,

58
00:03:26,816 --> 00:03:29,336
that's the purpose of the tree.

59
00:03:29,336 --> 00:03:31,968
The only reason the tree exists

60
00:03:31,968 --> 00:03:34,496
is to produce this fruit.

61
00:03:34,496 --> 00:03:39,497
Without this fruit what is that tree?

62
00:03:39,497 --> 00:03:41,575
When you taste this fruit

63
00:03:41,575 --> 00:03:46,234
then you can celebrate that tree in all it's fullness

64
00:03:46,234 --> 00:03:49,025
and understand: each part of it is glorious

65
00:03:49,025 --> 00:03:50,581
and really in some way...

66
00:03:50,581 --> 00:03:54,353
This is Guru Maharaj's ontological method

67
00:03:54,353 --> 00:04:01,501
of deciphering and going deeper into reality.

68
00:04:01,501 --> 00:04:08,380
So we're saying: if the Garuda-purana, for example, says:

69
00:04:08,380 --> 00:04:20,662
artho yam brahma sutranam, bharatartha vinirnayah,
gayatri bhasya rupo sau, vedartha paribrimhitah

70
00:04:20,662 --> 00:04:29,536
Saying... If it says, gayatri bhasya, this book with eighteen thousand shlokas.

71
00:04:29,536 --> 00:04:38,734
Eigthteen thousand shlokas commentary on one shlok?

72
00:04:38,734 --> 00:04:41,034
Or Gurudev said...

73
00:04:41,034 --> 00:04:44,698
When Guru Maharaj, I was prompting him

74
00:04:44,698 --> 00:04:49,953
to give the Gayatri explanation to record it,

75
00:04:49,953 --> 00:04:58,762
I was so excited and worried, I listened to the tape:

76
00:04:58,762 --> 00:05:03,099
I test the tape recorder as soon as he stops speaking

77
00:05:03,099 --> 00:05:06,012
to make sure I had it.

78
00:05:06,012 --> 00:05:07,742
There's another tape recorder and I can hear, like:

79
00:05:07,742 --> 00:05:13,818
I play it back in front of him to make sure.

80
00:05:13,818 --> 00:05:17,706
But when in the beginning, because I told Gurudev

81
00:05:17,706 --> 00:05:22,285
we're gonna do, we're like gonna get Guru Maharaj to like go in that direction

82
00:05:22,285 --> 00:05:24,731
and get in that mood and...

83
00:05:24,731 --> 00:05:39,149
And Gurudev said: one lakh shlok of Mahabharata in one shlok.

84
00:05:39,149 --> 00:05:44,205
gayatri bhasya rupo 'sau
vedartha paribrimhitah

85
00:05:44,681 --> 00:05:48,983

